Implemented a bounded Phase 2 repair in the existing pipeline and control surface. The key change is that hidden interaction risk is no longer inferred from authority entrypoints alone; it now tracks ownership depth, save/rollback tightness, and operator-visible traceability in the existing scorer and simulator at [architecture_pipeline.py](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/scripts/codex/architecture_pipeline.py#L166) and [architecture_pipeline.py](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/scripts/codex/architecture_pipeline.py#L620). I also tightened the hidden-risk mutation set there so repairs improve visibility and boundary discipline instead of only nudging one scalar.

On the runtime side, I exposed explicit ownership and mutation-boundary visibility through the current operator surface, without adding a new control plane: [metrics_aggregator.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/ops/metrics_aggregator.lua#L48), [economy_system.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/scripts/economy_system.lua#L288), and [session_orchestrator.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/ops/session_orchestrator.lua#L66). The targeted tests were updated to assert those surfaces in [ops_control_plane_test.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/tests/ops_control_plane_test.lua#L11), [economy_invariants_test.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/tests/economy_invariants_test.lua#L19), and [channel_transfer_integrity_test.lua](/home/meta_os/MapleWorld/tests/channel_transfer_integrity_test.lua#L12).

